summary: Another day, and welcome to the thirteenth post for the @sciencebrosbingo – Yep, I’ll go so fast with the bingo… But I don’t...
caption:
Another day, and welcome to the thirteenth post for the @sciencebrosbingo – Yep, I’ll go so fast with the bingo… But I don’t mind… I already have several bingo lines!! I’m so happy! xP Following the line of things I do, they will have design and text, longer or shorter depending on the moment. All will go under the cut in the posts.

-When you told me you wanted to take me to a special place, this wasn’t what I expected…- Bruce said moving slowly through the cemetery to which Tony had taken him, at least trying to be respectful, advancing while trying not to step on anything that he shouldn’t and holding both hands to avoid touching anything.
-I know, but I’ve been coming alone for years and now that I have a boyfriend, I didn’t want to have to keep doing it in that way.- Tony advanced until he reached the specific place.
-Ho… Yinsen…- Bruce read the name.- Did you tell me about him?- He wasn’t sure if Tony had ever done it.
-Nop.- Tony answered fast.- As I said, I always came here alone, it was something I preferred to do by myself… If it were not for him I wouldn’t be here… Possibly I wouldn’t have left alive from the cave of Afghanistan where they had me kidnapped.
-That was before being Iron Man…- Bruce said looking at Tony and getting a little closer to him from behind, running a hand down his back.
-That was when Iron Man was born. He saved my life, helped me to escape at the cost of his own life.
-Well, then… it’s something for which I should also thank him.

Before leaving, they left some fresh flowers on top of the stone and the humid ground because it had been raining only a few hours before. Then, they even stopped to eat and to toast for the life that still remained to them ahead, thanks to a brave man who helped Tony so much in the past.

title: say my name
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/31nEZ7k

by tornlinson

“I’m sorry?” He says finally, looking up at the man who suddenly looks very pleased with himself.

“My name is Loki,” the man repeats, “You need my name, don’t you?”

“You said it was Frank. Yesterday,” is all Loki says, but his eyes are narrowing in suspicion.

“Did I?” The man asks, tilting his head as he frowns, looking away. The man was doing a horrible job at pretending he didn’t know what Loki was talking about.

or, five times Tony doesn’t tell his name to the cute barista at Starbucks and one time he does (but the barista doesn’t believe him)
